snippet.textDisplay:
Jack in the Box is a fast food chain in the US with the toy clown as the figurehead of the company.
A jack in the box is a toy clown that springs out of a box when wound up.
You ain't jack is a way of saying you're a nobody.
Referring to someone as a jack in the box is also slang for saying a dead guy in a coffin.

"Only cap that you pop is the top on the can of your pop"

(referring to the previous line about rap being like a glock - Nick acts like he's strapped but he's not/he acts like he can rap but he can't)

"You the man 'till I pop yo' top, you ain't Jack in the Box"
(Nick's a clown...a dead one in rap)

"and I ain't talkin' about the hamburger spot, Cracker with a barrel"

(Em continues the references to soda pops and rap being like a glock by alluding to how Cracker Barrel got its name from actual soda crackers in physical barrels - ie how Em got his fame from being a talented white boy in the rap game (rap = glock, cracker = white boy, barrel = shotgun).

Since he's strapped with a barrel in the rap game, it's easy for him to pop caps at wanna-be rappers that can only pop soda caps.
